# Article Identification (Nunus)

When identifying or defining articles in this extension, follow these rules strictly:

## 1. Use ONLY the article's title

The article ID must be derived from the article's title. Never use URLs, slugs, or other identifiers as the article ID.

## 2. Use position for multiple occurrences

When the same article appears multiple times on a single page, use the article's position on the page to distinguish between occurrences.

## 3. URLs are for verification only

URLs may be used ONLY to verify that an element is indeed an article (e.g., matching URL patterns to filter out non-articles). URLs must NOT be used as the article ID or for storage keys.
